					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 14th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<extent>459 folios <dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>239</height>
										<width>161</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>142</height>
										<width>108</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>459 folios (+ 4 unfoliated modern paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end). Folio 1 is a paper flyleaf.</p>
									<p>Hebrew foliation in the upper left-hand corner of each recto.</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Indeterminable.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>Stained. </p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="37" writtenLines="36">
									<p>Uniform layout. Division into paragraphs (by a later hand) until no. 285 (folio 63r).</p>
									<p>Visible plummet ruling (each bifolium on both sides) and pricking.</p>
									<p>Last line written within ruling.</p>
									<p>Chapter initials given in larger square characters. </p>
									<p>Running headings.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Ashkenazi semi-cursive script of the 14th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Ya῾aḳov ben Yosef Blan</name>: inscribed in the colophon (folio 459v).</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole"/>
						</handDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Folio 459r: a responsum of R. <name type="person" role="author">Yosef of Orleans</name> on the subject of a divorce document.</p>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="owner">Natan Leṿi Adilkint</name> (?): inscribed, folio 2r.</p>
							<p>A description of the manuscript with a statement on the value of the text: folio 1v (paper flyleaf).</p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Black thick leather.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Mordecai Ben Hillel. Talmudic Expositions &amp; Decisions. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 19,972.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
